    "local_fix": "Change memcpy to use sizeof(structCharVoid->charFirst) as the copy size so only the 16-byte field is written. This prevents overwriting the adjacent pointer fields.",
    "global_fix": "Adopt a bounded field-copy helper or typed buffer wrapper (e.g., memcpy_s or a helper that deduces sizeof destination via an ARRAY_SIZE macro) so the destination field’s size is used and struct size cannot be confused with field size. This enforces correct bounds at the call site across the codebase."
